Story Premise Elias Vane returns to his childhood home after 28 years, following the deaths of his parents. As a child, Elias and his father fled the house suddenly, without explanation. 
He believed it was just a family move.  But upon his return, strange phenomena begin to unravel the truth: his mother, Margaret Vane, was involved in dark rituals and murdered Elias’s baby sister, Lilith.  
When confronted, Elias’s father killed Margaret in self-defense and fled with him.  Now, Margaret’s ghost haunts the house—not to stop Elias, but to finish what she started.

